00:00:44.740 --> 00:00:49.140
The first thing you need to take a case to
the Supreme Court is a case, or controversy,

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:52.690
and except in certain rare situations where
the court has original jurisdiction, that

00:00:52.690 --> 00:00:56.500
case has to have already heard and decided
by a lower court and appealed. And not just

00:00:56.500 --> 00:00:59.829
once; before a case gets to the Supreme Court
you have to have exhausted your appeals at

00:00:59.829 --> 00:01:03.440
lower levels of the state or federal system.
If you've lost your previous appeals but still

00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:06.310
think that you have an issue worthy of the
court's attention, you can petition for a

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:12.600
writ of certiorari, which people in the know call "the cert"
'cause they're keepin' it cash...which is short for casual.

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:17.200
For a look at how the court chooses its cases,
